    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How long does it take to sell a home in Moorooka?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Moorooka's affordability relative to Annerley and Greenslopes means there is a consistent and motivated buyer pool: first-home buyers who have been priced out of neighbouring suburbs, investors attracted by yield at a reasonable entry point, and young families looking for a free-standing home within five kilometres of the CBD. Well-priced properties in the residential streets attract strong first-week enquiry from this pool. Contact Daniel to discuss your specific property and timing." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the lifestyle like in Moorooka Brisbane?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Moorooka sits five kilometres south of the CBD with frequent Ipswich Road bus services connecting residents to the city. The suburb is bordered by Annerley to the north, Woolloongabba to the northeast, Rocklea to the south and Salisbury to the southeast, and it benefits from proximity to the shopping and cafe options along Annerley Road without carrying Annerley's price premium. The suburb is in transition, with sections of the commercial corridor evolving as investor and development interest has grown, but the residential streets remain a grounded, community-focused area." } },
