<!-- FAQ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Moorooka.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Moorooka?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Moorooka's affordability relative to Annerley and Greenslopes creates a consistent and motivated buyer pool. First-home buyers, investors and families all actively monitor the suburb, and a correctly priced property typically generates strong first-week enquiry from buyers who have been watching and waiting. The key is reaching all three buyer types simultaneously with a campaign structured for each.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Moorooka Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Moorooka is five kilometres south of the CBD with frequent Ipswich Road bus services providing a practical city commute. Annerley Road's cafes and shops are accessible to the north, and the suburb's residential streets are predominantly quiet and owner-occupied. The commercial and industrial fringe near Rocklea is in transition, with new residential development gradually changing the character of those edges. For buyers who want inner south proximity at a liveable price point, Moorooka has been delivering that combination for a number of years.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What types of homes are in Moorooka?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Moorooka has a genuine mix of post-war brick homes and original Queenslanders on established lots in the quieter residential streets, alongside a growing layer of townhouses and newer development near Ipswich Road and the commercial corridors. The free-standing home layer is what draws family buyers and owner-occupiers; the townhouse and unit layer is where investor yield interest is concentrated. Each type requires a different campaign approach to reach the right buyer pool.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Moorooka a good suburb for investment property in Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Moorooka draws consistent investor interest for several reasons: affordability relative to Annerley and Greenslopes, strong rental demand from professionals and young families who want inner south proximity, and an ongoing industrial-to-residential transition near the Rocklea boundary that has shifted the character of those streets over the past decade. As with any investment decision, the specific property and its position within the suburb matters considerably more than suburb-level commentary. Contact Daniel for an honest conversation about what your property achieves in the current rental and sales market.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

